      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, that's a really helpful breakdown of the criticisms. Looking at these points, it feels like the \"critics\" view is mostly based on a very rigid, text-only reading of the Constitution that might ignore the actual spirit of liberty. Do you think the arguments against substantive due process are ultimately just attempts to prevent the legal system from evolving alongside modern moral standards?",
